name: TE North/TGN-Eurasia/SEACOM/Alexandros/Medex
owners: Algerie Telecom, Cyta, PCCW, SEACOM, Tata Communications, Telecom Egypt
notes: Telecom Egypt operates TE North, but has sold fiber pairs to several parties. Tata Communications owns one fiber pair on the cable which the company refers to as TGN-Eurasia. SEACOM owns one fiber pair. Cyta owns one fiber pair and whollly-owns the branch to Cyprus which the company refers to as Alexandros. PCCW and Algerie Telecom operate a branch to Algeria called Medex.
